==English==
===Proper Noun===
'''P45'''
# (UK & Ireland) A [[form]] that an employee [[receives]] when they [[terminate]] their [[employment]]. A P45 details income for [[social security]] and [[taxation]] purposes for the current fiscal year. 

===Usage Note===
# To be given a P45 is to be [[sacked]] from [[employment]]
# To ask for a P45 is to [[resign]] from [[employment]]
# To be in [[possession]] of your P45 is to be without [[employment]]